        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why migrate to unified ai api gateway matters for fast-growing teams"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Teams searching for migrate to unified ai api gateway usually want two outcomes at once: lower cost per request and stable performance under real traffic. The fastest path is to design your API around measurable unit economics, not just benchmark demos."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Define a target gross margin and reject routes that break it."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Track latency, provider spend, and success rate by model and endpoint."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Separate baseline traffic from burst traffic before capacity planning."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Keep client-facing contracts stable even when provider routing changes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For migration plan decisions, this baseline prevents reactive architecture choices that look cheap short term but become expensive when usage compounds."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Architecture and routing pattern for cheap, scalable AI APIs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "High-performing API platforms route each request to the cheapest model that can still satisfy quality and latency goals. They also enforce auth, billing, and rate limits before expensive inference dispatch."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use OpenAI-compatible endpoints so client migration is low friction."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Apply model fallback order based on both quality threshold and effective cost."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Keep one model per endpoint where possible to isolate autoscaling behavior."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cache deterministic responses aggressively to reduce repeated GPU spend."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This pattern is cheapest when legacy clients are mapped to normalized endpoints."
